data.description: COMPLETELY RENOVATED move-in ready 4 bedrooms, 2 bath home with nearly 2,000 sq. Ft. and a NEW ROOF (June 2022).  FAMILY RELOCATING for career opportunity! Beautiful landscaping surrounds the entire home, it provides a serene setting and privacy.  As you walk through the front screened porch you are greeted by freshly painted double entry doors.  The foyer opens to the living and dining room, which showcases the brand-new luxury wood flooring that is upgraded through most of the home. The dining room includes a beautiful new elegant fixture.  So much natural light with several skylights throughout the home that have all been updated with hurricane resistant glass.  The kitchen features stainless steel appliances, upgraded granite, all new lighting fixtures, new back splash, wainscotting and lots of attention to detail. The large single basin sink with updated faucet has a pass-through window above it for convenience to the screened Lania and more sunlight.  The kitchen is the center of the home and conveniently extends right into the family room. Three spacious guest bedrooms, all including a walk-in closet, share the guest bathroom that is completely updated with gorgeous granite, fresh new paint color, and stunning oversized subway tile in the tub and shower combination.  Another skylight adds so much light and this bathroom has access to the back of the home for a future pool if that is your dream! The spacious primary suite is on the other side of the home from these bedrooms and enjoys privacy with this split floor plan.  It also includes 2 separate walk-in closets, ensuite bathroom features a linen closet, vanity, plus both a tub/shower and a walk-in shower. You will love the natural light that floods the bathroom through an additional skylight. The primary bedroom is one way to enter the oversized lanai space that feels like you are in a Zen Garden.  So much space for lounging or entertaining guests. The owners added a slightly elevated wood deck at the end of the lanai to showcase the hot tub and add to the setting.  From the lanai you can appreciate all the gorgeous landscaping which includes palm trees, banana, pineapple, lime, and a planter that will convey that grows herbs, onions and tomatoes. The 2-car garage houses the new A/C (2021) and water Heater (2021) as well as the laundry room (washer and dryer will convey). The electrical panel has also been updated. The home has been serviced quarterly for pests both inside and out. Another plus is the location, on a quiet cul-de-sac street where the neighbors are kind and friendly. Shopping and restaurants are minutes away. The Deep Creek community has easy access to I-75 in both directions. Deep Creek also offers golf, biking and walking paths and the community playground. Close by is historic downtown Punta Gorda and Fisherman’s Village where there are waterfront restaurants, farmers’ markets, art festivals and so much more. Don’t miss out on this prime location, schedule your showing today!
